summary: Email correspondence between a U.S. Attorney's Office official and others regarding a high-profile woman who called alleging past sexual assault by a man she believed was associated with Jeffrey Epstein. The woman was referred to the FBI but was skeptical about calling.

persons.name: Assistant U.S. Attorney Southern District of New York
persons.context: The sender of the initial email, relaying a call from a woman alleging sexual assault by an Epstein associate and requesting someone from the FBI reach out to her.

events.title: Victim Call to U.S. Attorney's Office
events.description: A high-profile woman called the U.S. Attorney's Office alleging she was previously sexually assaulted by a man she believed was associated with Jeffrey Epstein. She requested to speak with someone from the FBI.
personsInvolved: Assistant U.S. Attorney Southern District of New York

keyFacts: A high-profile woman contacted the U.S. Attorney's Office in July 2020 alleging past sexual assault by a man associated with Jeffrey Epstein.
The woman requested to speak with the FBI but was described as skeptical about calling the provided FBI number.
The correspondence shows ongoing victim outreach and investigation efforts related to the Epstein case after his death.
